<paragraph blockId="52.[136,1451,1886,2093]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Thallus corticolous, dichotomously branched, up to 
<quantity box="[744,803,1887,1913]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="cm" value="7.0">7 cm</quantity>
long, growing from a narrow holdfast. Branches solid, canaliculate,flat,smooth, 
<quantity box="[420,551,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="1.05" valueMax="1.7" valueMin="0.4">0.4–1.7mm</quantity>
wide.Pseudocyphellae marginal,linear.Soralia absent.Pseudocyphellae marginal, continuous, linear. Cortex indistinct. Chondroid tissue not cracked, continuous. Pycnidia not seen. Apothecia rounded, submarginal, up to 
<quantity box="[350,435,1994,2021]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
diameter, geniculate branches, discs concave to mainly flat. Ascospores multiseptate, longfusiform, 16–24 x 3–5 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[136,1451,1886,2093]" box="[189,1446,2066,2093]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,315,2066,2092]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Chemistry</emphasis>
(TLC, HPTLC): Traces of usnic acid only (Vareschi 4389) or nil (Vareschi 2783, 5451, 5932, 6182).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,487,158,184]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ecology and distribution</emphasis>
: This species grows on shrubs and orange trees in primary and secondary forests and subparamo at 
<quantity box="[293,451,194,221]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.36" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="1.3199999999999998" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="m" value="2360.0" valueMax="3400.0" valueMin="1320.0">1320–3400 m</quantity>
. It is known from South America (the Galápagos Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1168,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1222,1343,194,221]" name="Venezuela" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,298,230,256]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks</emphasis>
: Previously 
<taxonomicName box="[444,581,231,256]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="puiggarii">
<emphasis box="[444,581,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">R. puiggarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[851,919,230,256]" name="Brazil" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kashiwadani, H. &amp; Kalb, K." box="[936,1247,230,256]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref49971" refString="Kashiwadani, H. &amp; Kalb, K. (1993) The genus Ramalina in Brazil. The Lichenologist 25: 1 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282993000039" type="journal article" year="1993">Kashiwadani &amp; Kalb 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gumboski, E. L." box="[1260,1444,230,257]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref49145" refString="Gumboski, E. L. (2016) Estudos taxonomicos em especies de Ramalina Acharius (Ascomycota liquenizados, Ramalinaceae). Tese de Doutorado (Ph. D. dissertation), Universidade Federal do Rio Grande DO Sul, Instituto de Biociencias, Programa de Pos - Graduacao em Botanica Porto Alegre, 181 pp." type="book" year="2016">Gumboski 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and the Galápagos Islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Aptroot, A. &amp; Bungartz, F." box="[445,742,266,293]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="519 - 542" refId="ref47254" refString="Aptroot, A. &amp; Bungartz, F. (2007) The lichen genus Ramalina on the Galapagos. The Lichenologist 36: 519 - 542. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0024282907006901" type="journal article" year="2007">Aptroot &amp; Bungartz 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[760,1008,266,292]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="cumanensis">
<emphasis box="[760,1008,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ramalina cumanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1356,267,292]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="puiggarii">
<emphasis box="[1221,1356,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">R. puiggarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has shorter, uniseptate, ellipsoid spores (8–12 x 4–5 µm). 
<taxonomicName box="[730,991,302,328]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="camptospora">
<emphasis box="[730,991,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Ramalina camptospora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could also be confused with 
<taxonomicName box="[1310,1444,303,328]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Ramalinaceae" genus="Ramalina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="puiggarii">
<emphasis box="[1310,1444,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">R. puiggarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the former species has marginal soralia with isidiform structures, and curved or sigmoid spores (12–14 x 4–4.5 µm). All three species lack medullary substances.
</paragraph>
